<item>
            <title>[PIG-2059] PIG doesn&apos;t validate incomplete query in batch mode even if -c option is given</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2059</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Given the following in a file to Pig, pig doesn&apos;t report any error, even if -c option is given:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A = load &apos;x&apos; as (u, v);&lt;br/&gt;
B = foreach A generate $3;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s questionable whether to validate the query in batch mode as it doesn&apos;t contain any store/dump statement. However, if -c option is given, validation should be nevertheless performed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
